According to this page [1] to clone a wiki one must add "/wiki" to the repository URL. However doing so for me just clones the main repository. Am I using the wrong url?

{{{ hg clone  http://bitbucket.org/mercurialeclipse/main/wiki/ }}}

[1] https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BITBUCKET/Adding+Images+to+a+Wiki+Page

I would like to create a new issue from a commit message.\\
Commit that will contain something like:

{code}
TODO: fix language translation
{code}

should open a new issue - link this commit to it, and place in its name that line.\\
This issue should be created by the commiting user

an enhanced syntax could be:

{code}
TODO - somone@somewhere.com: fix translation for urdu
{code}

this could also give an assignee to that new issue
